# Day 4 – IAM Roles and Policies

## Overview
Today I learned how AWS Identity and Access Management (IAM) controls access to services using **users**, **roles**, and **policies**.  
IAM helps secure AWS resources by following the **least privilege principle** — giving only the permissions needed.

## Practice
### 1️⃣ IAM User
Created a new IAM user `test-user` and attached the **AmazonS3ReadOnlyAccess** policy.  
This user can view S3 buckets but cannot upload or delete files.

